{"type":"message","id":"3c8dc40f","parentId":"d992a4d0","timestamp":"2026-03-25T03:52:16.854Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reviewer final alignment report: REVISE (5 ❌, 2 🟡).\n\n**Issues to fix**\n1. Bibliography style: `\\bibliographystyle{plain}` → `IEEEtran`.\n2. `.bib` entry types: keys 1 (Goodfellow), 2 (Arjovsky), 3 (Gulrajani), 4 (Zhu), 5 (Odena) must change from `@article` to `@inproceedings`.\n3. Placeholder residues (≥10 numeric positions in `experiments_p1.tex`) must be filled with actual values.\n4. Method name inconsistency: replace all occurrences of \"ACWGAN-GP\" with \"CAC-CycleGAN-WGP\" (except when citing other works; ensure proposed method name is uniform).\n5. Table format: add `\\bottomrule` to `table4.tex` and `table7.tex` (they currently end with `\\midrule`).\n\n**Values already extracted from provided data**\n- Learning rate: 0.0001 (from `table_hyperparams.tex`)\n- Batch size: 64 (from `table_hyperparams.tex`)\n- Epochs: 500 (already in text)\n- PCC (Case I average, Sliding Window): 0.935 (computed from `table3.tex`)\n- Accuracies for Case I/II CNN at various BRs are available in `table5.tex` / `table6.tex`.\n\n**Missing numeric values (need user input)**\n- Training time (minutes) for 500 epochs.\n- Cosine Similarity (average for Case I).\n- ACGAN and WGAN baseline accuracies to compute the improvement differences stated for Case II (under IR=1:20).\n- Cross-domain performance gain (percentage).\n- Clarification: text mentions IR=1:10, 1:20, 1:50; our BR columns are 0.005, 0.01, 0.05, 0.25, 0.5, 1. Should we map IR=1:20 → BR=0.05, IR=1:50 → BR=0.01? The review did not question the numbers, only the placeholders; once numbers are provided we will insert them accordingly.\n\n**Planned actions after receiving numbers**\n- Create `drafts/v3` by copying `drafts/v2`.\n- Writer: method name replacement across all section files and fill all numeric placeholders.\n- Editor: update `generate_paper.py` to use `IEEE