{"type":"message","id":"f3990584","parentId":"ab9d9fe7","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:09:30.151Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to continue fixing the remaining issues. Let me summarize what still needs to be done:\n\n1. ✅ Reference cite format - FIXED\n2. 🔄 Concept figures (fig1-3) should be double-column - fig2 done, fig3 needs fix, fig1 missing\n3. ❌ Data figures - need to copy ALL user data images and stitch them together\n4. ❌ Layout alignment issues\n5. ✅ Conclusion shortened to one paragraph - FIXED\n\nLet me continue with:\n1. Fix fig3 (concept figure)\n2. Fix fig1 (concept figure) - needs to find where it's referenced\n3. For data figures - need to copy ALL images from user folders and create subfigures\n\nLet me start by finding and fixing fig3. The issue before was I couldn't find the exact text due to whitespace. Let me try a different approach.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n继续修复剩余问题：\n\n1. ✅ 引用格式 - 已完成\n2. 🔄 概念图 fig1-3 双栏 - fig2完成，fig3待修复，fig1缺失\n3. ❌ 数据图拼贴\n4. ❌ 排版对齐\n5. ✅ 结论精简 - 已完成\n\n继续修复fig3。先查找准确位置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2fb8b517c2e34434b91e904d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"SAE architecture\" /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":138522,"output":498,"cacheRead":272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139292,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774415348622}}
{"type":"message","id":"f1881ac0","parentId":"f3990584","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:09:30.163Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2fb8b517c2e34434b91e904d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"159:The SAE architecture, illustrated in \\begin{figure}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6,"aggregated":"159:The SAE architecture, illustrated in \\begin{figure}","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774415370158}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c77f38c","parentId":"f1881ac0","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:09:46.664Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it at line 159. Let me try to get the exact text around that line to do a proper edit.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f6acb9d5eafa4084be1aeb85","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex","limit":15,"offset":157}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":98226,"output":117,"cacheRead":40912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139255,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774415370163}}
{"type":"message","id":"c448b39b","parentId":"9c77f38c","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:09:46.671Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f6acb9d5eafa4084be1aeb85","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In the proposed framework, ensuring the physical consistency and diagnostic utility of the generated data is paramount. Traditional GAN evaluation metrics like the Inception Score (IS) or Frechet Inception Distance (FID) often fail to capture the subtle temporal and spectral nuances of industrial sensor signals, as they were originally designed for natural image datasets. Therefore, we employ a Stacked Autoencoder (SAE) as a dedicated quality evaluator to quantify the fidelity of the synthetic signals relative to the source domain distribution. Sparse Autoencoders, initially popularized by Ng \\cite{Ng2011}, are uniquely suited for this role due to their ability to reconstruct complex signal manifolds through a hierarchical feature extraction process, frequently analyzed using t-SNE \\cite{Maaten2008} for distribution verification.\n\nThe SAE architecture, illustrated in \\begin{figure}\n\\centering\n\\includegraphics[width=\\columnwidth]{fig3.png}\n\\caption{Figure Sae}\n\\label{fig:sae}\n\\end{figure}, consists of multiple layers of sparse autoencoders stacked to form a deep representation learner. Each layer is pre-trained to minimize the reconstruction error of its input, progressively extracting high-level abstract features from the raw time-series or frequency-domain data. The encoding stage compresses the input into a latent bottleneck, while the decoding stage attempts to recreate the original signal from this reduced representation. During the evaluation phase, the SAE is trained exclusively on the real data from the target domain $Y$. The fundamental assumption is that if the generator $G$ successfully captures the underlying distribution of domain $Y$, the generated samples $\\tilde{y}$ should yield a reconstruction error comparable to that of real samples.\n\nThe quality of a generated sample $\\tilde{y}$ is assessed using the Reconstruction Error Index (REI), defined as:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\text{REI}(\\tilde{y}) = \\| \\tilde{y} - \\text{SAE}(\\tilde{y}) \\|_2^2\n\\label{eq:rei}\n\\tag{9}\n\\end{equation}\n\n[322 more lines in file. Use offset=172 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774415386667}}
