{"type":"message","id":"639c9393","parentId":"c95e8830","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:13:52.680Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to continue fixing the remaining issues. Let me continue with the data figure concatenation using LaTeX subfigure environment. This is complex but necessary.\n\nI need to replace the current data figure references (fig4-fig10) with subfigure environments that combine multiple images.\n\nBut this is very complex to do manually. Let me think of a simpler approach:\n\n1. Use Python/PIL to actually combine the images into single composite images\n2. Then reference those composite images in LaTeX\n\nThis would be much easier than trying to manage subfigure in LaTeX.\n\nLet me try to combine the images using ImageMagick or Python.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"继续修复数据图拼贴问题。使用Python将每组子图合并为一张图：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c9bab3b120ac43e6add1dbc6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nfrom PIL import Image\nimport os\n\nsrc = \"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/data_fig\"\ndst = \"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3\"\n\nfor i in range(1, 9):\n    folder = f\"{src}{i}\"\n    if not os.path.exists(folder):\n        continue\n    \n    images = sorted([f for f in os.listdir(folder) if f.endswith('.png')])\n    if not images:\n        continue\n    \n    # Load images\n    imgs = [Image.open(os.path.join(folder, f)) for f in images]\n    \n    # Calculate dimensions for grid layout\n    n = len(imgs)\n    cols = min(3, n)\n    rows = (n + cols - 1) // cols\n    \n    w, h = imgs[0].size\n    new_img = Image.new('RGB', (cols * w, rows * h), (255, 255, 255))\n    \n    for idx, img in enumerate(imgs):\n        row = idx // cols\n        col = idx % cols\n        new_img.paste(img, (col * w, row * h))\n    \n    # Save combined image\n    new_img.save(f\"{dst}/combined_fig{i}.png\")\n    print(f\"Created combined_fig{i}.png ({len(images)} subimages)\")\n\nprint(\"Done!\")\nEOF"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":138229,"output":621,"cacheRead":272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139122,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774415602333}}
