{"type":"message","id":"26bf184e","parentId":"9ca89e78","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:21:47.250Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_549628d233a14bb8bec4b7a9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{amssymb}\n\\usepackage{booktabs}\n\\usepackage{multirow}\n\\usepackage{caption}\n\\usepackage{flushend}\n\\usepackage{balance}\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n\\title{CAC-CycleGAN-WGP: Imbalanced Bearing Fault Diagnosis via Cross-Domain Signal Translation with Wasserstein Gradient Penalty}\n\\author{Anonymous Author(s)}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4,"aggregated":"\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{amssymb}\n\\usepackage{booktabs}\n\\usepackage{multirow}\n\\usepackage{caption}\n\\usepackage{flushend}\n\\usepackage{balance}\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n\\title{CAC-CycleGAN-WGP: Imbalanced Bearing Fault Diagnosis via Cross-Domain Signal Translation with Wasserstein Gradient Penalty}\n\\author{Anonymous Author(s)}","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774416107247}}
{"type":"message","id":"570c3fef","parentId":"26bf184e","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:22:06.798Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"我之前移除了natbib，但现在IEEEtran需要使用内置的引用系统。让我检查bibliography部分并确保使用了正确的格式。另外需要检查是否有重复的figure和居中对齐问题。\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a5fcee71df2245bc914814e8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -10 /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":139165,"output":130,"cacheRead":1600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":140895,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774416107251}}
{"type":"message","id":"4fa35b52","parentId":"570c3fef","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:22:06.807Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a5fcee71df2245bc914814e8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\\section{Conclusion}\n\\label{sec:conclusion}\n\nIn this paper, we proposed CAC-CycleGAN-WGP, a novel data augmentation framework for imbalanced bearing fault diagnosis that combines cycle-consistent generative adversarial networks with Wasserstein gradient penalty and a conditional auxiliary classifier. Experimental results on two bearing datasets demonstrate that our method significantly outperforms state-of-the-art approaches, achieving over 98\\% accuracy under severe imbalance ratios while maintaining robustness across various operating conditions. Future work will explore deployment in real industrial environments and extending the framework to handle non-stationary operating conditions.\n\n\n\\bibliographystyle{IEEEtran}\n\\bibliography{references}\n\\end{document}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3,"aggregated":"\\section{Conclusion}\n\\label{sec:conclusion}\n\nIn this paper, we proposed CAC-CycleGAN-WGP, a novel data augmentation framework for imbalanced bearing fault diagnosis that combines cycle-consistent generative adversarial networks with Wasserstein gradient penalty and a conditional auxiliary classifier. Experimental results on two bearing datasets demonstrate that our method significantly outperforms state-of-the-art approaches, achieving over 98\\% accuracy under severe imbalance ratios while maintaining robustness across various operating conditions. Future work will explore deployment in real industrial environments and extending the framework to handle non-stationary operating conditions.\n\n\n\\bibliographystyle{IEEEtran}\n\\bibliography{references}\n\\end{document}","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774416126802}}
