{"type":"message","id":"9cc3d7fa","parentId":"e3fea815","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:30:21.638Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ed903730ecf54818bb0a8905","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\\documentclass[conference,twocolumn]{IEEEtran}\n\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{amssymb}\n\\usepackage{booktabs}\n\\usepackage{multirow}\n\\usepackage{caption}\nusepackage{balance}\nusepackage{flushend}\n\\% natbib removed\n\\% cite style removed\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n\\title{CAC-CycleGAN-WGP: Imbalanced Bearing Fault Diagnosis via Cross-Domain Signal Translation with Wasserstein Gradient Penalty}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3,"aggregated":"\\documentclass[conference,twocolumn]{IEEEtran}\n\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{amssymb}\n\\usepackage{booktabs}\n\\usepackage{multirow}\n\\usepackage{caption}\nusepackage{balance}\nusepackage{flushend}\n\\% natbib removed\n\\% cite style removed\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n\\title{CAC-CycleGAN-WGP: Imbalanced Bearing Fault Diagnosis via Cross-Domain Signal Translation with Wasserstein Gradient Penalty}","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774416621632}}
{"type":"message","id":"e820ef4e","parentId":"9cc3d7fa","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:30:34.894Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The backslashes are missing. Let me fix that.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cfafe1bd20484ec6bccca57d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -i 's/usepackage{balance}/\\\\usepackage{balance}/' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/usepackage{flushend}/\\\\usepackage{flushend}/' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/\\\\\\ natbib removed/\\\\textbackslash natbib removed/' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/\\\\\\ cite style removed/\\\\textbackslash cite style removed/' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\n\nhead -20 /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":812,"output":244,"cacheRead":142624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143680,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774416621639}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c30fd53","parentId":"e820ef4e","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:30:34.908Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_cfafe1bd20484ec6bccca57d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\\documentclass[conference,twocolumn]{IEEEtran}\n\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{amssymb}\n\\usepackage{booktabs}\n\\usepackage{multirow}\n\\usepackage{caption}\n\\usepackage{balance}\n\\usepackage{flushend}\n\\% natbib removed\n\\% cite style removed\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n\\title{CAC-CycleGAN-WGP: Imbalanced Bearing Fault Diagnosis via Cross-Domain Signal Translation with Wasserstein Gradient Penalty}\n\\author{Anonymous Author(s)}\n\\maketitle\n\n\\begin{abstract}\nRolling element bearings are critical components in industrial machinery, and their failure can lead to catastrophic system breakdowns. While deep learning has significantly advanced fault diagnosis, the performance of these models is often hampered by the class imbalance problem, where fault samples are scarce compared to normal data. To address this challenge, this paper proposes a novel framework termed CAC-CycleGAN-WGP for imbalanced bearing fault diagnosis. The methodological core involves a CycleGAN architecture that transforms normal vibration signals into realistic fault signals, integrated with a Conditional Auxiliary Classifier (CAC) to accurately capture the marginal probability distributions of various fault categories. To ensure training stability and suppress mode collapse, we incorporate Wasserstein distance with a Gradient Penalty (WGP). Furthermore, a quality assessment method based on Stacked Autoencoders (SAE) is developed to evaluate the fidelity of the generated samples. Extensive experiments are conducted on two imbalanced bearing datasets: the Case Western Reserve University (CWRU) dataset and a custom laboratory dataset. Comparative results against state-of-the-art methods, including SMOTE, GAN, WGAN, ACGAN, and CAC-CycleGAN-WGP, demonstrate that the proposed CAC-CycleGAN-WGP significantly improves diagnostic accuracy and robustness under severe data imbalance, providing a viable solution for real-world industrial health monitoring."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7,"aggregated":"\\documentclass[conference,twocolumn]{IEEEtran}\n\\usepackage{graphicx}\n\\usepackage{amsmath}\n\\usepackage{amssymb}\n\\usepackage{booktabs}\n\\usepackage{multirow}\n\\usepackage{caption}\n\\usepackage{balance}\n\\usepackage{flushend}\n\\% natbib removed\n\\% cite style removed\n\n\\begin{document}\n\n\\title{CAC-CycleGAN-WGP: Imbalanced Bearing Fault Diagnosis via Cross-Domain Signal Translation with Wasserstein Gradient Penalty}\n\\author{Anonymous Author(s)}\n\\maketitle\n\n\\begin{abstract}\nRolling element bearings are critical components in industrial machinery, and their failure can lead to catastrophic system breakdowns. While deep learning has significantly advanced fault diagnosis, the performance of these models is often hampered by the class imbalance problem, where fault samples are scarce compared to normal data. To address this challenge, this paper proposes a novel framework termed CAC-CycleGAN-WGP for imbalanced bearing fault diagnosis. The methodological core involves a CycleGAN architecture that transforms normal vibration signals into realistic fault signals, integrated with a Conditional Auxiliary Classifier (CAC) to accurately capture the marginal probability distributions of various fault categories. To ensure training stability and suppress mode collapse, we incorporate Wasserstein distance with a Gradient Penalty (WGP). Furthermore, a quality assessment method based on Stacked Autoencoders (SAE) is developed to evaluate the fidelity of the generated samples. Extensive experiments are conducted on two imbalanced bearing datasets: the Case Western Reserve University (CWRU) dataset and a custom laboratory dataset. Comparative results against state-of-the-art methods, including SMOTE, GAN, WGAN, ACGAN, and CAC-CycleGAN-WGP, demonstrate that the proposed CAC-CycleGAN-WGP significantly improves diagnostic accuracy and robustness under severe data imbalance, providing a viable solution for real-world industrial health monitoring.","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774416634902}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ea305e0","parentId":"6c30fd53","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:31:12.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are still some backslash issues with the comments. Let me fix those and then copy the combined images and compile.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_857c09a3ee094404a494a985","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Remove the bad comment lines\nsed -i '/\\\\\\\\_ natbib removed/d' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i '/\\\\\\\\_ cite style removed/d' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\n\n# Copy combined images\ncp /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/combined_fig*.png /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/ 2>/dev/null\n\n# Update figure references\nsed -i 's/fig4\\.png/combined_fig1.png/g' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/fig5\\.png/combined_fig2.png/g' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/fig6\\.png/combined_fig3.png/g' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/fig7\\.png/combined_fig4.png/g' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/fig8\\.png/combined_fig5.png/g' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/fig9\\.png/combined_fig6.png/g' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/fig10_part1\\.png/combined_fig7.png/g' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\nsed -i 's/fig10_part2\\.png/combined_fig8.png/g' /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-6/final/v3/paper.tex\n\necho \"Updated\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":66874,"output":578,"cacheRead":75872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143324,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774416634908}}
